      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:30:2",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) أَمَرَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) أَنْ لَا يُنْزَعَ شَيْ‏ءٌ مِنْ ثِيَابِ الْقَاذِفِ إِلَّا الرِّدَاءُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> ordered that nothing should be removed from the clothes of the slanderer except for the robe’."
        ]
      }
    }
